pageSummaryWhat: Every time I bake, I will donate
pageSummaryWhy: we never know when we might need them.
story:
As many of you know I bake, a lot. I wouldn’t say 365 days a year but it certainly feels like it sometimes! People with cancer or those caring for them do need support 365 days a year though. So, I thought that if I donated £1 every day for a year that would be £365. However, if for every bake I donate £1 on your behalf as well, I could maybe double that amount! 

It has been tough for everyone lately, with the current situation, but we sadly lost another very good egg this year. Joni’s legacy will live on in her many friends, family and those she helped through her role as Head of Learning at Edinburgh Science. Joni was a good friend and a strong supporter of my baking business. She was always first to Like my posts or to get enthused by treats I made her. She also adored lemon drizzle cake - one of my favourite bakes too. So, this is for Joni, for Sooz, for everyone who needs and receives support from Macmillan Cancer Support. 

I am not really asking for donations but obviously please do if you can and would like to.💕

So, thanks for supporting my fundraising. Macmillan Cancer Support is here to help everyone with cancer live life as fully as they can, providing physical, financial and emotional support. So whatever cancer throws your way, we’re right right there with you.Donating through JustGiving is simple, fast and secure. At the end of January 2021 I will be shaving my head to raise some funds for Macmillan. Macmillan Cancer Support is a fantastic organisation that help everyone with cancer live life as fully as they can, providing physical, financial and emotional support. 

I will be donating my hair to the Little Princess Trust. The Little Princess Trust provide free real hair wigs to children and young people, up to 24 years, who have lost their own hair through cancer treatment or other conditions.

charity.name: British Heart Foundation
story:
Thanks for taking the time to visit my JustGiving page.

As you may know, our mam Margaret passed away on12th December. The last couple of years hadn't been easy for her following problems with her heart and breathing, and towards the end of her life she struggled to walk.That didn't stop her doing what she wanted,however, ( galavanting around Darlington playing bingo and going to the club with her friends, much to our horror!)until the last few weeks when she unfortunately developed pneumonia and caught Covid 19. All of this, together with her heart and lung issues,  meant she wasn't able to pull through. She was 81.

Her funeral will be in Darlington in January.We have decided to only have immediate family flowers at the funeral,and would therefore like anyone who knew mam and would have sent flowers for her, to donate  to the British Heart Foundation instead. We hope to raise £250 for the charity in mam's name.

Thank you for all your support

Carol, Kev & all the family

xx

story:
Thanks for visiting my page. I'm raising money for the British Heart Foundation and I'd be so grateful for your support. 

Through the month of January, I'll be giving up alcohol and walking a mile everyday as part of my dry, rambley challenge.

The BHF has helped halve the number of people dying from heart and circulatory disease in the UK but sadly every day hundreds of people lose their lives. It's only thanks to support from people like us that the BHF can create new treatments and discover new cures. £24 could pay for two hours of research by an early career scientist, but every pound helps so please give what you can to help me hit my target. Thanks!

charity.name: British Heart Foundation
story:
This charity is particularly close to my heart. My dad has his first heart attack on his 61st Birthday back in the late 1980's. He recovered and went back to work at R.G.T.approx 6 months later. He had worked at RGT since leaving school. He took a deserved early retirement at 64, but only saw 4 years of retirement. He went out one Thursday morning in November 1994 to collect his and my Mum's pension only to never return. He died of a heart attack whilst collecting their pension. I was at work that morning in Lincoln and will never forget the phone call from home giving me the news.

He loved his football and cricket and took me to my first ever game at Sincil Bank to watch The Imps. I was stood on the West Bank terracing against the wall and it was chuffing freezing !! But I kept going back for more.

So after much deliberation I have decided to have a go at this challenge as I am now 61, the same age as my Dad when he had his first attack and feel should make an effort and contribute again to this worthy charity.The challenge also starts 2 days before his birthday.

Please give generously folk.

Many Thanks.

Go The Distance .100 Km . story:
Thanks for taking the time to visit my JustGiving page.

As you know my dad passed away at the start of 2020 it has been a tough year with the help of my friends and family I dealt with it.

As it's coming up to a year that he has been gone.

I have decided to do something to remember him by.

What I have decided to do is cycle 100 miles a month every month for the whole of 2021 so in total I will ride 1200 miles.

The 100 miles won't be done all in one go but will be over the whole month. I will keep how many miles I do updated on this group using my strava app I have.

I will be raising money for the British Heart foundation.

This has been a very tough year not just for me but for everyone so please give as little or as much as you can.

The link is below to donate.

story:
Thanks for taking the time to visit My Just Giving page.

So I had some news from my lovely neighbour last week that he has aggressive throat cancer.  He makes 4 people that I know are now suffering with cancer. My dad died of cancer 20 years ago and it's hard to see those I love to through this. 

I hope to raise money through walking the distance to contribute to the fight to treat and eradicate this awful illness. 

Please donate what you can. I'll update with progress reports as I complete distances. 

Thank you for your support.

eventName: Nico shaving his head (and my Dad if we raise enough)!
pageSummary: I am shaving my head because My mum’s cancer treatment has caused hair loss
pageSummaryWhy: My mum’s cancer treatment has caused hair loss
story:
Thanks for taking the time to visit my JustGiving page.

Hi all, on 18th September this year my Mum was diagnosed with Breast Cancer. She has been undergoing treatment and recently started chemotherapy. The chemotherapy helps to treat the cancer but it also makes her sick too. One of the side effects is that she is losing her hair and I have helped shave her head as it was already starting to fall out (she still looks great!). On New Year’s Eve, in support of my Mum, I am going to shave my head too and thought it would be a good idea to raise some money. I have chosen Cancer Research UK, it’s research contributes to better treatment globally. One in eight women will get Breast Cancer, two of my friends at Canterbury Rugby club have also experienced their mums getting Breast Cancer too. My target is £2500, my Dad has promised to shave his head too if we reach £5000 (I hope we do - he has an egg shaped head!!). Any support is greatly appreciated, Nico. 

(Using my Dad’s page as I am only 13)

pageSummary: January Double Marathon because Cancer took my mum and I want to help find a cure
pageSummaryWhy: Cancer took my mum and I want to help find a cure
story:
Hello All,,

Thank you for taking the time to get here! Please give me a few more minutes of your time to understand why I want to raise money for this worthy cause.

After my personal experience of  losing my mum to the horrible illness that is Cancer 3 years ago, I  want to help make sure we defeat this illness so no-one else has to lose a loved one like myself and many others have done.

I will be completing a running distance of equivalent to 2 London marathons which is 52.4 miles. As a current none runner and a Christmas diet behind me I will be pushing myself to complete this within the 30 days of January.  

I will be using the  Strava app to track my distance and times and will be keeping my page updated as I go along so you can follow the journey with me. 

I know 2020 has been a tough year for all of us and financially to most of us, that’s why every donation is appreciated more than ever and it doesn’t matter even if it’s £1 and all you can afford it is still going to help the cause. So please be generous and donate on here. EVERY donation is greatly appreciated from myself and thousands of others which Cancer has effected so far.

Thank you for reading.

Lots of Love,

Kieran x

story:
Hello Everyone! 

Thanks for taking the time to visit my JustGiving page. 

I am taking on a challenge! I will be taking on 26.2 miles in October 2021 in Budapest. This is as part of the Choose a Challenge Team who help us through the fundraising and training for the Marathon. I am raising money for Marie Curie. Marie Curie is the UK’s leading end of life charity. Providing frontline nursing and hospice care, a free support line and a wealth of information and support on all aspects of dying, death and bereavement. I have chosen to take this on to prove to myself that I can do it and cross that finish line and in the process do something good! 

 My goal is to raise £1000 for Hope for Children between now and August! I hope you can spare a couple of pounds for this charity!

I appreciate you taking the time to read and donate! :D

pageSummary: Hello friends and family, I am raising money because I want to help people who are suffering.
pageSummaryWhat: Hello friends and family, I am raising money
pageSummaryWhy: I want to help people who are suffering.
story:
This year has been difficult for many families around the world because of COVID 19. I read in the news that many children have lost their parents or grandparents. Many people have lost hope. Music gives me hope for the future, so from now till Christmas I will play a Christmas song on the cello each day and upload it on my YouTube channel to raise money for MSF. Please support me and help families that are affected by the coronavirus. Thank you!

Here's more information about MSF:

MSF's emergency teams are experts at fighting diseases all over the world. I'm raising funds to support the medical teams on the ground as they respond to coronavirus. MSF is providing urgently needed medical care and support in more than 70 countries. MSF's medical teams are also gearing up to confront potential outbreaks in the hundreds of areas they were already working before the pandemic struck.

pageSummary: I am asking friends and family  to please donate because to help towards clean water  for the whole  world
pageSummaryWhat: I am asking friends and family  to please donate
pageSummaryWhy: to help towards clean water  for the whole  world
story:
Hi everyone,

I hope you are all keeping well and that you have an enjoyable Christmas., and every blessing for the New Year. 

I can’t believe that it’s ten years since my 60 th birthday party ! and now just after New Year it’s my 70th !

I was going to have a party again like at my 60th. But now we will celebrate at home as a family .

I didn’t want any presents at my 60th but at this milestone I would love to do something different. Instead of celebrating with me and giving me presents I would like to ask you to donate to a worthy cause - WaterAid. Your donation will help towards providing clean water around the world and so save lives !

Thanks to everyone who is giving. You’ve help save babies’ and children’s lives around the world !

WaterAid say that a  third of the world’s population (2.3 billion) live without access to decent sanitation and 844 million are without access to clean water.

  • Some 289,000 children die each year from diarrhoeal diseases caused by dirty water and poor sanitation. That’s almost 800 children each day, or one child every two minutes.

Give before 4 February 2021 and your donation will be doubled by the UK government, up to £2 million, making double the difference in climate-vulnerable communities.
